text: Daniela Mincă (born 14 July 1971) is a Romanian volleyball player, playing as a setter. She was part of the Romania women's national volleyball team. She competed at the 1993 Summer Universiade, winning a gold medal, and the 2001 Women's European Volleyball Championship. In 2014, she was Romanian Volleyball Player of the Year. She won the Romanian League championship in 2005/06, 2003/04, 1996/97, 1995/96, 1994/95, and 1993/94. She played for CS Rapid București. == References == Category:1971 births Category:Living people Category:Romanian sportspeople Category:Volleyball players
